n about the park in winter!" - Christina Ergler is the first one to explore why `play' resonates differently across urban localities and seasons. She draws on Bourdieu's theory of practice and Gibson's affordance theory to show that determinants of seasonal outdoor play transcend modifiable barriers such as traffic and unsuitable play spaces as well as the inevitable issue of inclement weather. In contrast, seasonal play determinants are grounded in locally constituted beliefs about what is seasonally `appropriate' children's activity. To foster a healthier and more sustainable life for children, outdoor play needs to become convenient all-year-round in all locations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aBourdieu. 4aCultural Geography. 4aGeography. 4aIndependent Mobility. 4aObesity. 4aPhysical Activity. 4aPlace. 4aPlayground. 4aSeason. 4aSocial Geography. 4aSpace. 4aYouth. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Human Geography.2bisacsh  aBourdieu.  aCultural Geography.  aGeography.  aIndependent Mobility.  aObesity.  aPhysical Activity.  aPlace.  aPlayground.  aSeason.  aSocial Geography.  aSpace.  aYouth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020 Englishz978311070475408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020z9783110704556oZDB-23-DPC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttra